A general view of the outside of a COVID-19 ward at  Hospital in Cape Town. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa has reported 6,170 new COVID-19 cases in the last 24 hours. 27,310 tests were conducted in the same period which represents a 22.6% positivity rate. READ: COVID-19 vaccine plant risks closure due to lack of orders The Department of Health has reported 30 deaths; of which 2 occurred in the past 24 to48 hours. The total number of fatalities now stands at 100,407.